  "time_ut": 1657271997,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0db9\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0dbd\u0dd0\u0db6\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dd4 \u0d91\u0dc5\u0dc0\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0ddd \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3 \u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dc3\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dambulla gets 200,000 kilos of vegetables per day",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The situation that the daily supply of vegetables to the Dambulla Economic Center has dropped from twenty lakh kilos to two lakh kilos and the crisis faced by the farmers is a situation created by this government and that the All Ceylon Farmers' Federation will support the farmers in order to avoid the immediate expulsion of the current government that has destroyed the farmers. Organizer Mr. Namal Karunaratne said today (08th) in Dambulla.",
        "Mr. Namal Karunaratne came to Dambulla to observe the situation of businessmen, farmers and middlemen of Dambulla economic center these days.",
        "First, the manager of the Economic Center Management Trust, Christy Wijeratne, the president of the Trade Association, U.B. After discussing the current market situation with Mr. Ekanayake, Mr. Namal Karunaratne went to the market and started discussing trade with farmers, businessmen and artisan traders.",
        "There, many farmers said that due to lack of fuel, they are unable to bring vegetables to the Dambulla Economic Center. Also, the farmers said that they are facing a serious situation of not being able to sell their crops due to the decrease of traders coming from outside regions to buy vegetables.",
        "It is special that Mr. Namal Karunaratne observed how large quantities of jackfruit that had been brought to the Dambulla Economic Center were not sold and were piled up to be destroyed.",
        "After this, Mr. Namal Karunaratne who addressed the journalists said that the current government should accept the responsibility of destroying agriculture completely.",
        "He said that Mr. Gotabhaya Rajapaksa is currently hiding from the fear of the people and that the farmers will join hands and implement the Farmers' Congress to oust the current government.",
        "After Mr. Namal Karunaratne's statement to the media was over, an intermediary businessman who came to the place said that no one would come in this way even when the price of vegetables rises. mentioned.",
        "Mr. IG Wijenanda, who was a businessman of Dambulla economic center, while explaining to Mr. Namal Karunaratne, said that since about 30 years, everyone is facing this problem because it has not been implemented even though it has been proposed to prepare an agricultural policy in this country. He stated that whoever comes to power must implement a necessary agricultural policy."
      ],
